1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,161
I have an idea!

2
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:40,707
If Agent Alex wants to stay here with us,

3
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:42,876
then she should be willing to put up with

4
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:45,587
<i>whatever she ends up hearing.</i>

5
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:52,635
Luisa Mae is Laurence's girlfriend?

6
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:53,636
You're a couple!

7
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:59,225
No, we actually have more
of a connection with Angelito.

8
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,113
Because between two women, Alex,

9
00:01:27,504 --> 00:01:29,589
Mikoy loves watching soap operas.

10
00:01:29,672 --> 00:01:32,383
Even I'm starting to enjoy them.

11
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:41,684
But what I don't like is,
they always throw in a third party.

12
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:58,034
But I can't really blame you.

13
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,995
It's not hard to like Mikoy.

14
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,289
Actually, he's easy to love.

15
00:02:06,292 --> 00:02:07,418
But right now,

16
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:09,838
it doesn't matter anymore.

17
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:15,885
It doesn't matter who
or how many people have fallen for him.

18
00:02:17,095 --> 00:02:18,429
What's important is,

19
00:02:19,013 --> 00:02:20,932
Mikoy chose me…

20
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,812
and I'm the one he loves.

21
00:02:37,657 --> 00:02:39,200
Then in that case,

22
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:41,870
you have nothing to worry about.

23
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:03,766
Why did you suddenly go quiet?

24
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,269
Did we interrupt something?

25
00:03:06,811 --> 00:03:09,105
Looks like you were gossiping about us.

26
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:15,028
Sweetheart, we were just talking about
how lovable you are,

27
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:18,656
and how you make this stay less boring.

28
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:23,578
I thought it was something serious.

29
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:24,913
And of course,

30
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:26,915
everybody loves me.

31
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:28,625
I'm the life of the party, you know.

32
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:31,669
Of course!

33
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,431
There we go!

34
00:03:43,514 --> 00:03:44,682
So my kiss passed the test?

35
00:03:45,725 --> 00:03:48,144
Looks like I'll make it into
the top three next time.

36
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:53,691
Oh, here.

37
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:11,167
Hey.

38
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,168
Why, bro?

39
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:13,836
While they're busy,

40
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:15,838
there's something I want to tell you.

41
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:21,302
Not now. I still have a lot
to clean up from the tortilla stand.

42
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:23,179
This will be quick, I promise.

43
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:24,430
I really just need your help.

44
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,057
Help?

45
00:04:27,934 --> 00:04:30,103
- Why me?
- You're friends with Sofie, right?

46
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:33,815
Is this about

47
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:36,359
what you told her earlier?

48
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,153
That you want her to say yes?

49
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:41,656
Yes.

50
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:45,660
Angelito. I want to court Sofie.

51
00:04:46,744 --> 00:04:48,079
Can you help me?

52
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:51,082
Come on.

53
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:55,795
Okay.

54
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:57,213
Thank you.

55
00:04:58,756 --> 00:04:59,632
Bestfriend.

56
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:45,511
I really can't take it anymore.

57
00:05:47,221 --> 00:05:48,389
So noisy.

58
00:05:49,015 --> 00:05:50,183
So noisy.

59
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:17,043
The scenery is actually nice at night.

60
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,170
You can clearly see the stars.

61
00:06:20,254 --> 00:06:21,881
Unlike in the city.

62
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:43,236
What are you doing, sweetheart?

63
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,987
I'm catching a star.

64
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,949
I want to make a wish.

65
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,832
Let me help you

66
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:57,708
so you can make more wishes.

67
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:00,878
There.

68
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,008
Here, this one's cute.

69
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:18,104
Wow! There are so many!

70
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:22,150
There!

71
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,943
So you can make more wishes.

72
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,236
Right?

73
00:07:33,077 --> 00:07:34,454
What do you wish for?

74
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:42,086
My wish is,

75
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:48,009
that the two of us will finally be free.

76
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:52,305
No agency.

77
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:55,099
No Concordat.

78
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:57,477
No safehouse.

79
00:07:58,102 --> 00:08:00,229
No safehouse mates.

80
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:05,026
Just the two of us.

81
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,656
In our own world.

82
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,341
Good thing I already got my star.

83
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:14,262
Oh, please!

84
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,013
That's so cheesy.

85
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:20,226
Admit it, you got butterflies.

86
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:34,240
When did you realize you liked Sofie?

87
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,245
It's more than just liking her.

88
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:41,998
It's like…

89
00:09:42,081 --> 00:09:43,249
Like what?

90
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,544
Like I love her.

91
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:48,838
That fast?

92
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,089
You already love her?

93
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:51,632
Are you even close?

94
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:53,301
I mean,

95
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:57,179
haven't you only spent
a little time together?

96
00:09:58,514 --> 00:09:59,724
You know, Angelito,

97
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:02,810
I've always believed that

98
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,521
it's not really about how long
you've known someone

99
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:07,189
to love them.

100
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:09,734
And I admit

101
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:13,946
that Sofie and I have only
spent a little time together.

102
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:16,532
But honestly,

103
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:21,912
I feel sad when she's sad.

104
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:26,417
I do everything I can to make her happy.

105
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:28,878
Now tell me,

106
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:31,881
if this isn't love,

107
00:10:31,964 --> 00:10:34,592
then what is it? Madness?

108
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:38,471
I don't know either.

109
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:45,144
But wait, what kind of
help do you want from me exactly?

110
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,650
Just kidding. Seriously though.

111
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:52,860
Me too.

112
00:10:53,569 --> 00:10:55,196
Of course I miss that too.

113
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,698
Just the two of us.

114
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,661
Away from all the noise of the world.

115
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:06,332
But you know,

116
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:11,128
maybe this is actually
a good opportunity for us.

117
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,633
Because we can't spend
our whole lives running.

118
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:18,260
Right?

119
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,599
Like you said,

120
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:26,727
we have families,

121
00:11:28,562 --> 00:11:29,939
friends,

122
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:35,277
people who love us,

123
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:42,368
and we can't turn our backs on them.

124
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:46,622
Maybe,

125
00:11:47,623 --> 00:11:48,666
this,

126
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:51,460
us staying here,

127
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:56,841
might be the first step toward
returning to them someday.

128
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:06,058
And don't think
that's no longer what I want.

129
00:12:08,102 --> 00:12:10,146
Of course I love being alone with you.

130
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:12,440
Of course.

131
00:12:14,066 --> 00:12:15,484
If it were up to me,

132
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,611
we'd stay hidden forever.

133
00:12:19,738 --> 00:12:21,157
But…

134
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:25,494
But sooner or later,

135
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:31,709
we have to face the music of life.

136
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:57,193
Are you serious?

137
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:16,253
Just remember this.

138
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:18,339
In the darkness,

139
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:22,051
the stars shine even brighter.

140
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:01,275
You know, Angelito,

141
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:03,777
I'm aware that

142
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:06,238
you and Sofie
have a weird friendship, right?

143
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:10,117
You've told me all about it.

144
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,036
And more importantly,

145
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,455
you probably know that

146
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:18,459
I don't want to be a jerk of a friend.

147
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:23,756
Because the bro code is important to me.

148
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:28,636
Now let me ask you.

149
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:31,722
Are you and Sofie just friends?

150
00:15:35,142 --> 00:15:36,477
Of course.

151
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,811
We're just friends.

152
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:41,607
You don't listen to my rants, do you?

153
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:45,778
- Really?
- Yes.

154
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:48,155
It's probably not too late
to confess, right?

155
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:53,035
That's right. We're just friends.

156
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:57,873
Especially after we found out that

157
00:15:57,957 --> 00:16:02,086
our parents were actually
friends too, a long time ago.

158
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:04,296
Since they were kids.

159
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:06,131
- Really?
- Exactly!

160
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:07,967
You know Sofie,

161
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:11,345
she's practically my sister.

162
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,430
Really?

163
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,390
Yes.

164
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:21,772
Here. Mama Tess sent this over,

165
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:24,566
so you'd have something to go with
the drink you're having.

166
00:16:25,526 --> 00:16:26,735
Thank you, Sofie.

167
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,362
Would you like to sit down first?

168
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:31,532
No, I still have something to do upstairs.

169
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:47,733
<i>And what's on her mind again?</i>

170
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:53,924
<i>The sunlight is perfect,</i>
<i>so forget what you saw last night.</i>

171
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:56,135
<i>Don't let it affect you.</i>

172
00:18:57,010 --> 00:19:00,722
<i>You're here for the mission.</i>
<i>You are disciplined.</i>

173
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:05,477
<i>It's just a feeling,</i>
<i>you are Special Agent Alex.</i>

174
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:43,140
<i>Remember, Alex, you can't lose any fight.</i>

175
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:26,516
Let's not get out of bed.

176
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:45,077
Is that okay?
Is that the boneless one? Just kidding.

177
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,995
- Is it seedless? Seedless?
- Yes, ma'am.

178
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,789
Are you sure? Because what if…

179
00:20:49,373 --> 00:20:51,041
What is this? Why is…

180
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:52,417
Why is Aquaman here too?

181
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:55,170
You've turned my house into
some kind of co-working space.

182
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:37,337
Have you found the two of them yet?

183
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:39,339
Not yet, Ma'am.

184
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:42,175
But we've already sent people to the place

185
00:21:42,259 --> 00:21:44,136
where we suspect they're hiding.

186
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:46,513
Good.

187
00:21:46,596 --> 00:21:51,351
Report to me once you find them.

188
00:22:23,175 --> 00:22:24,718
<i>Where are you Chiara?</i>

189
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:42,212
I would just like to remind you
that you need to update ASAP.

190
00:23:42,295 --> 00:23:45,799
Because Senator Quintin will have a
briefing with our President.

191
00:23:45,882 --> 00:23:47,634
Okay, I'll send it once I finish it.

192
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:49,177
Agent Alex, there's a problem!

193
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:51,805
What?

194
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:55,892
You're so annoying.

195
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:02,941
Do you like jelly beans?
I found it in the pantry.

196
00:24:03,024 --> 00:24:03,942
Maybe you want some.

197
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:22,085
At this point, we still don't know why
La Morte Bianca is building the site.

198
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:23,587
We're not sure yet.

199
00:24:23,670 --> 00:24:26,715
If you really want to know what they know,

200
00:24:27,674 --> 00:24:30,427
we need to talk to one of their people.
